Add esm support to emotion

Same as with rebase components.

- emotion.js
- emotion.mjs
- index.js
- index.mjs

`main` is referenced to dist/index.(js|mjs)
`/emotion` is referenced to dist/emotion.(js|mjs)

Proxy '/emotion' with package.json

This is more universal solution unlike mjs. The idea is simple.
package.json may also specify any field and bundler accessing its
directory will be redirected to dist.

This prevents reexport for both emotion cjs and esm bundles.

I also renamed es to esm since es is used sometimes to distribute
es6+ code. esm is more descriptive.

Run jest only from the root

This allows to reduce configuration and modules count per each package.

All dependencies (except rebass and styled-system) are reused from the
root. With yarn workspaces all depenendecies could be hoised without
need to remove them from each packages. That's why I removed evenr react
packages.
